  "response": "In general, money laundering involves financial transactions designed to conceal the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by passing it through legitimate businesses or bank accounts. Key elements usually include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's source\n3. Integration: Making the funds appear legitimate\n\nSpecific legal definitions can vary by jurisdiction. For precise details, I recommend consulting local legal resources or a qualified attorney.",
